--- a/docs/architecture.md
+++ b/docs/architecture.md
@@ -299,6 +299,10 @@ newlines and Shift+Enter are chat prompt line breaks. A plain Enter submits the
 When an agent chat is selected in command mode, `/` focuses the chat, seeds the chat buffer with
 `/`, and enters insert mode so `/status`-style input submits through the same selected-agent chat
 path.
+In command mode, `v`, `V`, and `Ctrl-V` start character, line, and block visual selections for the
+focused pane. `h/j/k/l` and the arrow keys move the visual cursor, `Esc` clears the selection, and
+`y`/`Y` yanks the selected text. Terminal adapters queue yanked text through OSC 52 clipboard output;
+the UI harness stores the same text in its yank register for automatic tests.
 
 The terminal app maps a session to a left-pane `READY` marker when the controller exposes no loading
 state for that session. `TerminalUi` queues one terminal bell when a chat transitions into the ready
